Description of Contents:

Ankur_Thesis_Upload.pdf: A copy of my final master's thesis containing a description of my research

Paper1_search.m: Code for estimating the number of samples required to estimate a bandlimited field with less than 1% detection error probability

Paper1_sim.m: Code for comparing the performance of different distributions on sensor locations for bandlimited field estimation from location-unaware sensors

Paper1_sim_noisy.m: Code for estimating a bandlimited field using location-unaware sensors and including corruption of samples by Gaussian noise

segment_em.m: Implementation of EM algorithm for clustering noisy samples

signal.m: Generation of a real-valued periodic bandlimited signal of a given bandwidth

Publications:
Ankur Mallick, Animesh Kumar. "Bandlimited field reconstruction from samples obtained on a discrete grid with unknown random locations." IEEE International Conference on Acoustics, Speech and Signal Processing (ICASSP), 2016. (Oral Presentation) 
Link: http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/xpl/articleDetails.jsp?arnumber=7472431
Ankur Mallick, Animesh Kumar. "Bandlimited Field Reconstruction from Samples Obtained at Unknown Random Locations on a Grid." submitted (under review) to IEEE Transactions on Signal Processing.
Link: https://arxiv.org/abs/1611.10211
